# Default deny; only the rules listed below are permitted.

# sensor01 (the Pico): publishes sensor readings, receives both the
# read-now request and the actuator commands. The Pico hosts the heater
# and cooler relays alongside the DHT22, so it needs read on every
# actuator topic the controller publishes to.
user sensor01
topic write sensor01/data
topic read sensor01/request
topic read heater01/data
topic read cooler01/data
topic read actuator01/data

# controller: ingests sensor readings, dispatches actuator commands and
# sensor requests. Actuator IDs come from the actuator_commands table
# (LSTM writes heater01 / cooler01, dashboard or operator may write
# actuator01 manually). Listed explicitly rather than wildcarded so an
# attacker who somehow controls the DB cannot pivot to $SYS topics.
user controller
topic read sensor01/data
topic write heater01/data
topic write cooler01/data
topic write actuator01/data
topic write sensor01/request
